{
  "text": "For each sample, two 1.5 mm diameter samples of dried blood (equivalent to 3-5 \u00b5L of blood) [CITATION_1] were placed in the well of a 96-well PCR microplate (Axygen Scientific, Union City, CA). Each plate included two positive controls (P. vivax or P. falciparum) and three negative controls (two blood spots from a known malaria negative donor and one no-template reaction control). To remove haemoglobin, 70 \u00b5L of molecular biology grade water (Cellgro-Mediatech INC, Manassas, VA) were added to each well and the plate was incubated at 50 \u00b0C for five min, 21 \u00b0C for 15 s, 50 \u00b0C for 1.5 min, and 21 \u00b0C for 15 s. The water was then removed from each well and discarded.",
